Always apply these rules when writing code in this project:

## Language & Stack
- PHP 8.2+, strict_types=1 in every file
- No framework — custom platform with PSR-4 autoloading (App\ → src/)
- Bootstrap 5, jQuery 3.7 frontend
- MySQL 8.0+ with InnoDB, utf8mb4_unicode_ci

## Database
- Use `App\Core\Database` PDO wrapper: `fetchOne(sql, params)`, `fetchAll(sql, params)`, `execute(sql, params)`
- Never raw `$mysqli->query()` with string interpolation
- Always named params: `['id' => $id, 'org_id' => $orgId]`
- Table names: Use `DB::CUSTOMERS`, `DB::INVOICES` — never hardcode `erp_customers`
- Every query must include `organization_id` scoping

## Architecture
- Controller → Service → Repository → Model (readonly DTO)
- New classes go in `src/{Layer}/` under `App\{Layer}` namespace
- Models: `readonly class Name(...)` with constructor promotion
- Throw `App\Exception\*` exceptions, never `die()` or `exit()`

## Security
- CSRF via `validate_csrf_token()` on every POST
- Permissions via `granted('action', $module_id)` or `granted_('action', 'slug')`
- Use `App\Security\InputValidator` for user input
- Session: `$_SESSION[$project_pre]['DASHBOARD']`

## Do NOT
- Add package.json or Node.js tooling
- Add a PHP framework
- Use SELECT *
- Use @ error suppression
- Write markdown docs unless asked
- Add comments unless requested
- Hard-delete records (use is_active=0)

## Layout & UI Standards
- **External CSS**: Do NOT use inline CSS styles. Refactor all layout and style overrides to the external compatibility stylesheet (`dashboard/assets/assets_custom/css/haipulse-dashboard-compat.css`).
- **Page Header Layout**:
  - Keep `.page-header` block display (full width).
  - Use `.page-header-content` with flex display, `justify-content: space-between`, `align-items: center`, `flex-direction: row`, and `flex-wrap: nowrap` to split header elements (title on the left, action/CRUD buttons on the far right).
  - On edit/create pages, place the page header directly under `.content-wrapper` (outside the `<form>` element) so it spans the full width. Connect the header's submit button to the form using the HTML5 `form` attribute (e.g., `form="frmcarriers"`).
- **DOM Hierarchy**:
  - Keep `.content-inner` as a direct child of `.content-wrapper` to preserve scroll container behavior.
  - Put `<form>` inside the `.content` div, wrapping only the inputs/cards, rather than wrapping the entire page.
- **Copyright Alignment**: Place the copyright file include (`include('admin_elements/copyright.php');`) at the very bottom of `.content-inner` (directly after `.content` closes) to align it correctly at the bottom of the page flow.
